constructor.details: Overrides parent contract URI with Polis-specific metadata.

params._status: Oikos status: 0 - token deactivated, 1 - in property, 2 - is being used, 3 - on sale, 4 - in project.

params._parentUnityId: Id of Unity (if exists, can be empty).

params._maxStatus: Max status of Oikos to be listed (if needed to filter).
params._minStatus: Minimal status of Oikos to be listed (if needed to filter).

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._newOwnerAddress: New address of the same real-world owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setRemintingPermission(uint256,bool).details: Available only to the owner of token.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

getOikosList(uint16,uint16,uint8,uint8).notice: Get list of Oikoses which form given Polis.

getOikosStatus(uint256).notice: Returns the status of the Oikos token.

getParentPolis(uint256).notice: Get Polis in which Oikos resides.

remintOikosToken(uint256,address).notice: Remint (disactivate old and create new) token in case if owner lost access to his account (private key). Can be run only by the owner of the contract.

setRemintingPermission(uint256,bool).notice: Grants or revokes permission to remint the token.
